Menu

[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" border_width="2" el_width="10" accent_color="#b5d3ab"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

Russian Tea

I love this tangy beverage on a cold winter's morning when I want something tasty and hot, but don't want coffee! It makes a great gift from your kitchen, too!

Whisky Tea

This is how my grandad makes his cups of tea. He's in his seventies now and drinks whisky like he'll never get hold of it again.This drink is very relaxing.

Friendship Tea

This is a lemony spiced tea mix with cinnamon and clove that makes great gifts during the holidays, or any time!

Cranberry Tea

You can use sugar or equal. Keeps in refrigerator and heat as you want. This is sweet and tangy.

Adeni Tea

This recipe come from Aden, Yemen. Its great for a weekend brunch or breakfast. Sweet, rich, authentic, fragrant, and magical hot drink.[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="40" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="bottom-to-top"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]
